{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Trend Micro |model=JewelryBox |revision=(TMJB-010) |ean=4988752015755 |asin= |price= |est_release_date= |fcc_date=09/03/2013 |manuf_country=China |manuf=Alpha Networks |manuf_model=ADM671 |manuf_rev= |availability=now |type=media player |fcc_id=RRK-TMJB010 |ic_id=4833A-TMJB010 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=1 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Sigma Designs |cpu1_model= |cpu1_cspeed= |fla1=512 MiB |fla1_brand=Samsung |fla1_model=K9F4G08U0D-SCB0 |fla2=16 GiB |fla2_brand= |fla2_model=SD |ram1=512 MiB |ram1_brand=Nanya |ram1_model=NT5TU128M8GE-AC |ram1_num=4 |expansion_if_types=USB 2.0, microSD, SD Card, |expansion_usb_num=1 |jtag= |serial= |wi1_module=Alpha Networks WUS-N10M |wi1_module_if=USB (non-standard connector) |wi1_chip1_brand=Ralink |wi1_chip1_model=RT3070 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=1 |wi1_rxchains=1 |wi1_sstreams=1 |eth_none= |eth_cpu=true |eth_chip2_brand=IC+ |eth_chip2_model= |lan_speed=100M |lan_ports=1 |wan_ports= |flags=HDMI out |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ssid= |default_ssid_regex= |default_ip= |default_user= |default_pass= |oui= |oui_eth= }} "ADM671M" and "8ADM671M..2A1G" is silkscreened on the main board in the FCC photos. :"8WUSN10M.0B1G" is silkscreened on the wireless module. :"8ADM671D.2A1G" and "ADM671D" is silkscreened on the SD Card + USB breakout board. The device seems to have an internal microSD slot. :RAM is set as being ''NT5TU128M8GE-AC''s, but this is probably wrong. :P/N seems to be NT5TU128...AC though
The power supplies shown included with the device in the FCC photos are... *'''US (NEMA 1-15P)''': '''Asian Power Devices Inc.''' WA-12L12FG :(100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 0.5A max. -> 12VDC, 1A) *'''UK''': '''Asian Power Devices Inc.''' WA-12L12FK :(100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 0.5A max. -> 12VDC, 1A) *'''AUS''': an '''Asian Power Devices Inc.''' WA-12L12FN :(100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 0.5A max. -> 12VDC, 1A)
